- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithmic questions and presents a new algorithm for finding a minimum size feedback vertex set in a tournament.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper deals with graphs and their properties.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possibility as the paper deals with tournament graphs, which are commonly used in game theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly discuss complexity theory, but it may still be relevant as the paper presents upper and lower bounds on the maximum number of minimal feedback vertex sets in a tournament.
